Defendant Alexia A Morrison in court, in custody, with attorney Katie B. Kegel.   Melissa J. Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State makes sentencing recommendations.  Defense makes sentencing recommendations.  Court reads VIP statement from Barbara Sproule.  Attorney Kegel requests expungement.  State objects.  Court denies the request for expungement.    The Defendant was given the following:
Count 3

WITHHELD SENTENCE;

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  the victim or her residence listed in the Criminal Complaint
*Shall never work in the caregiving field

RESTITUTION:  $15,461.00 (to be paid to Chubb Insurance - to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);
                          $15.00 (to be paid to Chase Bank - to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to paid before costs or fines);
COURT COSTS:  $278.00 (includes $10.00 DR GOD surcharge - to be paid as a condition of probation);
DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

CONDITION TIME: 12 MONTHS HUBER, the last 7 months are STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  
Defendant is currently in custody and is to serve 5 months.  Credit time 82-days.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
